comment: Remote stop for isolation of T26 Transformer
Stopped for TX Replacement on T26
Gearoil cold/superheated fault - Confirmed via energy export that turbine was back in tun at 2pm - Stop ended to reflect this
site trip-Mark Jones from SSEC to attend at 1530 hrs 28/04
Internal planned outage for T07 transformer replacement works
T32 Transformer failure. Replacement to be arranged.
In surrender. Seized pipework requires further attention.
HV outage for Transformer Oil sampling

Awaiting windspeeds to drop below 12m/s for 2+hours before reset is possible
2 hour monitor of windspeed. If average below 12m/s then reset.
DWT cannot access Turbine due to weather. Techs to return 17/01
Remote reset attempted - Escalated to DWT 28/01
Suspected damage to bearings in gearbox as vib analysis test failed following drive train analysis. Oil sample tests and final gearbox inspection report awaited
Gearbox has been replaced. Awaiting alignment and connections to be completed
